00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:00,501 --> 00:00:04,963
I need to know the truth
about Hijikata Toshizo.

2
00:00:05,088 --> 00:00:09,218
He had the same look in his eyes as you.

3
00:00:09,718 --> 00:00:13,639
What's the fun
in doing the sensible thing?

4
00:00:13,764 --> 00:00:17,851
Doing what no one else
can is what makes you a badass.

5
00:00:18,435 --> 00:00:19,853
It was the final years of Edo.

6
00:00:22,314 --> 00:00:26,693
There were men who lived fiercely
and passionately by the way of the sword.

7
00:00:27,236 --> 00:00:30,197
To become the strongest man there is.

8
00:00:30,322 --> 00:00:33,450
What a coincidence. Same here.

9
00:00:36,286 --> 00:00:41,708
I welcome you as the fools who are ready
to die alongside the Aizu!

10
00:00:43,001 --> 00:00:46,255
They pressed on with unwavering resolve
against the tide of history.

11
00:00:50,759 --> 00:00:53,220
This is the story of the last samurai

12
00:00:54,388 --> 00:01:00,435
men who bloomed brilliantly
in an age of turmoil, and then fell.

13
00:01:01,186 --> 00:01:02,896
Let us bloom with all our might.

14
00:01:07,276 --> 00:01:13,198
SONG OF THE SAMURAI

15
00:01:13,323 --> 00:01:18,370
SONG OF THE SAMURAI

16
00:01:23,667 --> 00:01:29,047
APRIL 1862, TOSA

17
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:36,972
Man, Edo is amazing!

18
00:01:38,849 --> 00:01:41,226
It was packed with people,
and the food was delicious.

19
00:01:41,351 --> 00:01:44,229
And, what's more, there were
a ton of strong fighters, too.

20
00:01:44,813 --> 00:01:49,109
But Toshi was
the strongest out of them all.

21
00:01:49,401 --> 00:01:52,988
You just told us that story about Toshi.
That's the fifth time.

22
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:57,075
Is that true, Ukichi?

23
00:01:57,200 --> 00:02:01,246
But still, Izo, since it makes you laugh

24
00:02:01,371 --> 00:02:03,582
I'd be happy to hear it five or six times!

25
00:02:03,707 --> 00:02:05,208
Hey!

26
00:02:06,376 --> 00:02:10,589
Never mind all that.
Did you get a taste of this?

27
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:15,177
What? Do you eat pinkies?

28
00:02:15,302 --> 00:02:19,890
You idiot! Edo has Yoshiwara,
the land's greatest pleasure district!

29
00:02:20,015 --> 00:02:24,436
I'm talking about women!

30
00:02:24,561 --> 00:02:29,274
I'm... not very good with women.

31
00:02:29,399 --> 00:02:32,486
I've never seen or "tasted"
anything like that.

32
00:02:37,866 --> 00:02:41,411
Hey, Izo!
Master Takechi is calling for you!

33
00:02:45,791 --> 00:02:47,084
Assassination?

34
00:02:47,918 --> 00:02:49,336
Keep your voice down, Izo.

35
00:02:50,337 --> 00:02:52,381
But still, an assassination...

36
00:02:54,132 --> 00:02:56,301
It's divine retribution, Izo.

37
00:02:57,427 --> 00:02:58,595
Divine retribution?

38
00:02:59,805 --> 00:03:02,099
We are to eliminate Yoshida Toyo.

39
00:03:04,476 --> 00:03:05,602
Who is that?

40
00:03:06,895 --> 00:03:08,980
You don't even know who Toyo is?

41
00:03:09,398 --> 00:03:12,734
He's the ringleader in Tosa
who oppresses lower-class samurai like us.

42
00:03:13,443 --> 00:03:16,154
He sides with the shogunate's plan
to open the country

43
00:03:16,738 --> 00:03:19,783
a vile man who is leading
our nation to ruin.

44
00:03:21,368 --> 00:03:22,369
Izo.

45
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:26,707
You, too, are a member
of the Tosa Loyalist Party.

46
00:03:30,001 --> 00:03:31,461
Lend me your strength

47
00:03:32,796 --> 00:03:34,381
to restore the emperor
and expel the foreigners.

48
00:03:51,898 --> 00:03:55,485
No, I can't do that. Anything but that.

49
00:03:55,610 --> 00:03:57,279
Izo!

50
00:03:57,404 --> 00:03:59,531
You would really turn down Master Takechi?

51
00:04:00,449 --> 00:04:03,660
But I don't like killing people.

52
00:04:04,953 --> 00:04:05,996
I'm sorry.

53
00:04:07,789 --> 00:04:09,666
- Hey! Get back here, Izo!
- Wait, Izo!

54
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:11,585
- Let him go.
- But, Master Takechi...

55
00:04:12,419 --> 00:04:14,629
Well, wait and see.

56
00:04:25,307 --> 00:04:26,975
Why would anyone do this?

57
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:31,813
Ukichi!

58
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:38,236
Ukichi!

59
00:04:42,824 --> 00:04:44,409
Ukichi.

60
00:04:44,534 --> 00:04:45,619
Ukichi.

61
00:04:46,787 --> 00:04:48,747
They were making an example
of Ukichi's father!

62
00:04:50,207 --> 00:04:53,585
He petitioned the domain
to lessen the burden of the labor tax.

63
00:04:56,171 --> 00:04:57,506
And the one who gave the order

64
00:04:59,424 --> 00:05:00,634
had to be Yoshida Toyo.

65
00:05:03,512 --> 00:05:04,763
That damn Toyo!

66
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:07,849
How much more will he make us suffer?

67
00:05:41,174 --> 00:05:42,551
Ukichi.

68
00:05:45,971 --> 00:05:47,180
Ukichi.

69
00:06:02,529 --> 00:06:03,572
I...

70
00:06:07,659 --> 00:06:09,244
will avenge...

71
00:06:13,081 --> 00:06:14,374
you.

72
00:06:19,629 --> 00:06:21,298
I'm sorry, Ukichi.

73
00:06:24,342 --> 00:06:25,719
I'm sorry, Izo.

74
00:06:46,615 --> 00:06:48,658
Yoshida Toyo, this is divine retribution!

75
00:07:00,795 --> 00:07:03,506
Do you think a bunch
of Loyalist Party monkeys

76
00:07:05,008 --> 00:07:06,885
can take me down?

77
00:07:14,225 --> 00:07:15,310
Why?

78
00:07:17,729 --> 00:07:18,939
Why...

79
00:07:20,649 --> 00:07:22,859
Why did you kill Ukichi?

80
00:07:24,027 --> 00:07:25,946
Another one, huh?

81
00:07:27,614 --> 00:07:28,740
Ukichi...

82
00:07:31,117 --> 00:07:33,995
looked up to me like an older brother.

83
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:37,624
What is this nonsense you're spouting?

84
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:41,419
You die first!

85
00:07:48,677 --> 00:07:51,054
Impossible that a lowly samurai...

86
00:07:53,723 --> 00:07:57,102
could be this skilled...

87
00:08:00,772 --> 00:08:01,940
Izo!

88
00:08:02,691 --> 00:08:04,067
You did it!

89
00:08:04,317 --> 00:08:07,112
It's divine retribution!

90
00:08:07,654 --> 00:08:08,947
You did it, Izo!

91
00:08:18,707 --> 00:08:20,750
And that was the beginning
of Izo the Manslayer.

92
00:08:22,836 --> 00:08:28,633
After that,
following Takechi Hanpeita's orders

93
00:08:29,426 --> 00:08:31,720
he cut down one key shogunate official
after another.

94
00:08:35,265 --> 00:08:36,683
So he was

95
00:08:37,225 --> 00:08:41,187
a completely different man from when
he met my grandfather, Hijikata Toshizo.

96
00:08:41,771 --> 00:08:46,276
A different man? That's putting it mildly.

97
00:08:48,403 --> 00:08:52,574
When a man with a kind soul
is forced to keep killing brutally

98
00:08:52,699 --> 00:08:55,785
do you know what happens to him?

99
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:03,418
He shatters.

100
00:09:04,502 --> 00:09:05,920
Hold it!

101
00:09:06,046 --> 00:09:07,130
KYO, ONE YEAR LATER

102
00:09:08,131 --> 00:09:10,175
Surrender, Izo the Manslayer!

103
00:09:11,843 --> 00:09:12,927
Stay away.

104
00:09:15,138 --> 00:09:16,514
Don't come near.

105
00:10:23,957 --> 00:10:25,875
Hey... Hey!

106
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,669
Hey, what's going on?

107
00:10:27,919 --> 00:10:28,920
The Mibu Ronin are coming.

108
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:30,880
The Mibu Roshigumi?

109
00:10:31,005 --> 00:10:34,801
Check out that cocky bastard strutting
at the very front.

110
00:10:34,926 --> 00:10:37,679
Rumor is he killed Tanaka Shinbei.

111
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:40,306
- Hijikata Toshizo, the vice-commander?
- Yes.

112
00:10:40,974 --> 00:10:42,350
Toshizo?

113
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:47,856
- Hey, they're coming.
- Yeah.

114
00:11:28,229 --> 00:11:29,606
What's up, Toshi?

115
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:33,568
I feel like we're being watched.

116
00:11:35,111 --> 00:11:36,571
A loyalist assassin?

117
00:11:39,032 --> 00:11:40,950
No, it's probably nothing.

118
00:12:06,935 --> 00:12:10,355
By this time, the Mibu Roshigumi had grown

119
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:13,983
and was split into two major factions.

120
00:12:15,526 --> 00:12:18,571
The first was led
by Commander Kondo Isami...

121
00:12:18,696 --> 00:12:19,864
One!

122
00:12:19,989 --> 00:12:25,078
...with Vice-Commanders Hijikata Toshizo
and Yamanami Keisuke

123
00:12:25,536 --> 00:12:27,288
the Shieikan faction.

124
00:12:28,081 --> 00:12:30,917
- One, two!
- One, two!

125
00:12:31,042 --> 00:12:35,463
- One, two!
- One, two!

126
00:12:36,089 --> 00:12:39,717
The other was the Serizawa faction,
led by First Commander Serizawa Kamo

127
00:12:40,551 --> 00:12:42,971
Vice-Commander Niimi Nishiki

128
00:12:43,930 --> 00:12:49,936
and Assistant Vice-Commander
Hirayama Goro.

129
00:12:51,271 --> 00:12:52,897
Don't tell me

130
00:12:53,940 --> 00:12:59,696
they went out drinking again
last night and still aren't back.

131
00:13:01,698 --> 00:13:04,993
Those bastards!

132
00:13:05,118 --> 00:13:06,953
Incredible!

133
00:13:07,078 --> 00:13:09,038
Mr. Todo sure is impressive!

134
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:11,207
How about that, Shimada?

135
00:13:13,084 --> 00:13:15,962
SHIMADA KAI

136
00:13:16,087 --> 00:13:17,964
Damn, Shimada!

137
00:13:18,089 --> 00:13:19,090
Like a god of war!

138
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:23,428
Hey, Shimada! Don't get cocky, rookie!

139
00:13:24,012 --> 00:13:25,930
I'm sorry. I got a little carried away.

140
00:13:26,055 --> 00:13:29,475
Put those down, now! Put those down!

141
00:13:29,726 --> 00:13:31,978
All of you, drop and give me push-ups!

142
00:13:33,521 --> 00:13:34,564
Mr. Yamanami.

143
00:13:41,571 --> 00:13:47,702
- 11, 12, 13
- 11, 12, 13

144
00:13:47,827 --> 00:13:54,792
- 14, 15, 16...
- 14, 15, 16...

145
00:14:00,798 --> 00:14:02,467
You want to switch to the other faction?

146
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:06,804
Tell me why.

147
00:14:08,097 --> 00:14:11,184
I wish to train under Master Serizawa.

148
00:14:12,143 --> 00:14:15,688
They see more action,
and they're flush with cash.

149
00:14:16,147 --> 00:14:19,233
Plus, it's fun.
They get to party almost every night.

150
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:21,486
- Exactly.
- Exactly.

151
00:14:23,154 --> 00:14:24,530
So that's the real reason, huh?

152
00:14:31,662 --> 00:14:32,997
Well, yeah. That makes sense.

153
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:37,752
Fine.

154
00:14:38,836 --> 00:14:39,837
Do whatever you want.

155
00:14:41,339 --> 00:14:42,382
Are you serious?

156
00:14:42,507 --> 00:14:44,675
Yeah, but..

157
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:47,136
on one condition.

158
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:50,807
Wake up, Gen!

159
00:14:52,350 --> 00:14:53,643
It's starting again!

160
00:14:57,188 --> 00:14:58,439
Yes.

161
00:14:59,690 --> 00:15:03,528
Well, look who's all here.

162
00:15:04,195 --> 00:15:06,572
Hey, it hasn't started yet, right?

163
00:15:06,697 --> 00:15:07,907
It starts now.

164
00:15:08,199 --> 00:15:09,409
Hey

165
00:15:10,159 --> 00:15:11,411
come at me all at once.

166
00:15:13,246 --> 00:15:15,164
If you can land just one strike on me

167
00:15:16,165 --> 00:15:18,668
you can go to Serizawa's group
or wherever the hell you want.

168
00:15:18,793 --> 00:15:19,794
Awesome.

169
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:21,504
Not confident, even four against one?

170
00:15:21,838 --> 00:15:24,340
If you're that pathetic,
they won't give you the time of day.

171
00:15:27,051 --> 00:15:30,096
Hijikata, mind if we add three more?

172
00:15:30,221 --> 00:15:31,514
Yeah, I don't care.

173
00:15:32,265 --> 00:15:33,266
That's seven men!

174
00:15:33,391 --> 00:15:35,518
But even for Mr. Hijikata, that's...

175
00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:40,231
Hey.

176
00:15:41,274 --> 00:15:44,110
- On guard!
- C'mon, take it seriously!

177
00:15:44,235 --> 00:15:46,112
What are you, scared? Hey!

178
00:15:46,237 --> 00:15:48,364
- There are seven of us! We can win this!
- Yeah!

179
00:15:48,489 --> 00:15:50,616
- Good luck.
- Yeah.

180
00:15:53,411 --> 00:15:56,164
Get him!

181
00:16:03,713 --> 00:16:06,340
What's the matter? Bring it!

182
00:16:13,181 --> 00:16:14,182
Hey.

183
00:16:16,267 --> 00:16:17,435
So, I take it you're all staying?

184
00:16:19,395 --> 00:16:22,690
Whoa! Look at you go, Toshi!

185
00:16:24,317 --> 00:16:28,905
That was pathetic, you guys. Gen.

186
00:16:30,615 --> 00:16:31,699
What is this?

187
00:16:33,284 --> 00:16:34,285
Hey!

188
00:16:34,410 --> 00:16:35,703
I'll assist you.

189
00:16:38,331 --> 00:16:40,249
So it's against you two?

190
00:16:43,002 --> 00:16:45,338
Now this is getting interesting.

191
00:17:16,369 --> 00:17:17,370
Dammit!

192
00:17:17,495 --> 00:17:18,746
Hey, it's not a lethal blow.

193
00:17:18,871 --> 00:17:20,289
Awesome!

194
00:17:20,414 --> 00:17:22,458
Damn. He got me!

195
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:25,545
Man, what were you thinking?

196
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:28,589
What's the matter?
Are you that pissed you lost to me?

197
00:17:28,756 --> 00:17:32,885
That's not it! You won the fight
against those guys, didn't you?

198
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:35,221
So why did you run them all off?

199
00:17:35,346 --> 00:17:37,974
If they want to leave,
there's no use trying to stop them.

200
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:41,102
That's so like you, Toshi.

201
00:17:41,352 --> 00:17:43,563
There you go again, being so nonchalant.

202
00:17:43,688 --> 00:17:47,400
Do you know how many men
we've lost to them this month?

203
00:17:47,525 --> 00:17:49,026
Pardon the intrusion.

204
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:53,614
You must all be tired.
Please help yourselves.

205
00:17:54,782 --> 00:17:56,534
Perfect timing.

206
00:17:57,243 --> 00:17:58,661
You're always so thoughtful, Aijiro.

207
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:02,290
Not at all. I'm honored
you remembered my name, sir.

208
00:18:03,249 --> 00:18:06,669
What are you so tense about?

209
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:10,298
He's never this well-behaved around me.

210
00:18:10,423 --> 00:18:13,759
Even in the last practice,
he mercilessly beat me down.

211
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:15,136
That's not right.

212
00:18:15,261 --> 00:18:17,305
The one always beating me down
is you, Master!

213
00:18:17,430 --> 00:18:19,890
See? He's usually got
a much bigger mouth on him.

214
00:18:20,016 --> 00:18:23,477
What's this?
Bragging about your cute little disciple?

215
00:18:30,359 --> 00:18:31,694
But

216
00:18:31,819 --> 00:18:33,446
is this really okay?

217
00:18:34,405 --> 00:18:36,824
For someone like me,
the son of a craftsman

218
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:39,952
to join the Mibu Roshigumi?

219
00:18:42,455 --> 00:18:44,457
If you can't join our ranks

220
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:46,917
then we'd all have to quit on the spot.

221
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:49,086
Right, Toshi?

222
00:18:50,755 --> 00:18:52,923
We're just farm boys ourselves.

223
00:18:54,842 --> 00:18:55,843
Aijiro...

224
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:58,638
being a samurai isn't
about your social status.

225
00:19:00,389 --> 00:19:01,557
It's about what's in here.

226
00:19:06,437 --> 00:19:09,065
Commander Kondo, everyone...

227
00:19:09,190 --> 00:19:13,944
I swear I'll make myself useful
to all of you!

228
00:19:15,446 --> 00:19:17,406
Good. See that you do, Kojiro.

229
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:19,867
- It's Aijiro.
- Yeah, I know.

230
00:19:21,035 --> 00:19:22,370
Thank you.

231
00:19:25,539 --> 00:19:28,209
Man, that's something else.

232
00:19:30,461 --> 00:19:33,673
That master-disciple bond, you know?
It gets you right here.

233
00:19:33,798 --> 00:19:36,884
Seriously, I'm so damn jealous.

234
00:19:37,593 --> 00:19:39,136
I want one of those, too.

235
00:19:39,470 --> 00:19:40,930
What the hell do you want?

236
00:19:42,431 --> 00:19:43,808
Hey, Saeki!

237
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:46,143
What are you doing skulking around here?

238
00:19:46,268 --> 00:19:49,689
What about your patrol?
You're supposed to be on duty today!

239
00:19:50,898 --> 00:19:52,149
Oh, that's right.

240
00:19:52,316 --> 00:19:54,360
SAEKI MATASABURO

241
00:19:54,485 --> 00:19:56,904
I heard he was out again last night.

242
00:19:57,655 --> 00:19:59,990
You know, what's-his-name.

243
00:20:00,116 --> 00:20:03,327
What was it again? Uzo? Muzo?

244
00:20:06,163 --> 00:20:09,959
Izo! That's it, Izo. Okada Izo.

245
00:20:11,794 --> 00:20:14,505
He was prowling Tominokoji last night.

246
00:20:15,548 --> 00:20:16,799
Tominokoji?

247
00:20:19,427 --> 00:20:21,053
You can just leave him to me.

248
00:20:22,346 --> 00:20:24,682
If you don't dispose of thugs
like him quickly

249
00:20:24,807 --> 00:20:27,017
a man can't enjoy his sake in peace.

250
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:29,478
Are you trying to pick a fight?

251
00:20:30,479 --> 00:20:32,022
What's that supposed to mean?

252
00:20:32,857 --> 00:20:34,859
Okada Izo is a manslayer, you know.

253
00:20:37,570 --> 00:20:40,656
Or is he a "friend" of yours,
Vice-Commander?

254
00:20:41,157 --> 00:20:44,952
In fact, isn't protecting him the same
as picking a fight with our Aizu patrons?

255
00:20:47,913 --> 00:20:50,040
Saeki isn't wrong about any of this.

256
00:20:50,166 --> 00:20:51,459
This isn't right, Toshi.

257
00:20:51,584 --> 00:20:52,710
Saeki.

258
00:20:54,044 --> 00:20:55,546
I apologize for the trouble.

259
00:20:57,256 --> 00:21:01,051
But Toshi would never do anything
to endanger the corps.

260
00:21:01,177 --> 00:21:02,303
You can count on that.

261
00:21:04,513 --> 00:21:09,393
I need you to give it your all
as a Vice-Commander's Assistant.

262
00:21:12,563 --> 00:21:14,732
Well, I can't exactly say no
to the commander, can I?

263
00:21:15,107 --> 00:21:16,942
Well, then, I'll be off on my patrol.

264
00:21:31,582 --> 00:21:35,002
Boss! Why is he the same rank as me?

265
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:36,212
Settle down.

266
00:21:37,630 --> 00:21:39,632
Saeki's attitude isn't something
to be proud of.

267
00:21:40,674 --> 00:21:43,594
But you've noticed it as well, I'm sure.

268
00:21:45,638 --> 00:21:47,598
His killing intent is not
to be taken lightly.

269
00:21:48,182 --> 00:21:52,019
We'll likely see more men of his ilk
joining our ranks from now on.

270
00:21:52,728 --> 00:21:55,689
Yeah, we're getting more and more guys
with murky pasts.

271
00:21:56,649 --> 00:21:59,610
It's increasingly difficult
to maintain control.

272
00:22:02,696 --> 00:22:04,949
We may need to take some measures.

273
00:22:35,729 --> 00:22:39,608
Looks like the master of this place
has agreed to our "donation."

274
00:22:53,747 --> 00:22:55,082
Come on, have a drink.

275
00:22:55,207 --> 00:22:59,712
Master Serizawa,
you should train us sometime.

276
00:22:59,837 --> 00:23:03,924
It's always booze and women with you.
Our enemies will walk all over us.

277
00:23:07,303 --> 00:23:10,598
Oume, go ahead and train him.

278
00:23:10,723 --> 00:23:13,851
- Me? Are you sure?
- Yeah.

279
00:23:14,852 --> 00:23:16,061
Are you...

280
00:23:17,563 --> 00:23:18,939
really that strong?

281
00:23:20,274 --> 00:23:21,650
You're always drunk off your ass.

282
00:23:23,110 --> 00:23:24,570
I bet even I could take you.

283
00:23:26,697 --> 00:23:31,160
I may not look it, but I've cut down
a Hokushin Itto-ryu master, too.

284
00:23:32,786 --> 00:23:35,247
Is that right? Heh.

285
00:23:36,040 --> 00:23:39,209
All right, I like your nerve.
I'll give you a lesson.

286
00:23:42,755 --> 00:23:45,257
Try to kill me. Right now.

287
00:23:46,967 --> 00:23:48,260
Hell, if anything

288
00:23:49,386 --> 00:23:51,472
I'll even fight you bare-handed.

289
00:23:53,891 --> 00:23:56,143
I'm the chief commander of the Mibu Ronin.

290
00:23:56,268 --> 00:23:58,729
If you take me down,
you'll be famous overnight.

291
00:23:58,854 --> 00:24:02,149
The Imperialists might pay you a fortune.

292
00:24:02,608 --> 00:24:03,776
Or perhaps...

293
00:24:07,613 --> 00:24:11,742
are you afraid of me,
even when I'm unarmed?

294
00:24:19,792 --> 00:24:20,918
Don't you mock me.

295
00:24:26,090 --> 00:24:27,091
Come on.

296
00:24:32,638 --> 00:24:36,684
Hey, do you all get it now?
This is how I train.

297
00:24:37,351 --> 00:24:39,770
Come try to kill me
whenever you want. Got it?

298
00:24:45,401 --> 00:24:47,695
I'll follow your lead, Serizawa!

299
00:24:47,820 --> 00:24:49,863
Pour it over my hand.

300
00:25:04,837 --> 00:25:07,131
You're pretty damn good.

301
00:25:08,007 --> 00:25:09,842
You've got some skills yourself.

302
00:25:12,553 --> 00:25:15,431
We'll have another match, Toshizo.

303
00:25:16,348 --> 00:25:17,433
Sure.

304
00:25:23,897 --> 00:25:27,818
You. What are you doing here?

305
00:25:35,159 --> 00:25:36,285
You're...

306
00:25:37,870 --> 00:25:39,079
Okada Izo.

307
00:25:39,580 --> 00:25:40,664
Izo?

308
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:46,462
Don't come.

309
00:25:49,673 --> 00:25:51,008
You mustn't come.

310
00:25:54,887 --> 00:25:56,013
Don't come.

311
00:25:59,391 --> 00:26:01,018
You mustn't come.

312
00:26:12,905 --> 00:26:14,198
Again.

313
00:26:23,624 --> 00:26:25,000
A manslayer...

314
00:26:27,002 --> 00:26:28,295
A manslayer like me...

315
00:26:33,717 --> 00:26:34,885
has no right...

316
00:26:38,430 --> 00:26:40,057
to show up

317
00:26:41,183 --> 00:26:42,392
before Toshizo.

318
00:26:57,449 --> 00:27:00,994
I guess it was after you all passed by.

319
00:27:01,829 --> 00:27:03,872
He was rummaging through scraps

320
00:27:03,997 --> 00:27:07,084
and other trash for food to eat.

321
00:27:07,209 --> 00:27:08,794
Eating trash?

322
00:27:08,919 --> 00:27:13,715
Yeah. It was a ghastly sight to see.

323
00:27:20,389 --> 00:27:21,974
It was right here.

324
00:27:51,003 --> 00:27:53,172
Will you let me know if you see him again?

325
00:27:57,050 --> 00:27:59,011
Before the magistrate's office.

326
00:28:01,388 --> 00:28:02,472
Got it?

327
00:28:03,098 --> 00:28:04,349
Understood.

328
00:28:08,061 --> 00:28:09,313
It's the manslayer again!

329
00:28:09,438 --> 00:28:13,150
Move out of my way!

330
00:28:18,155 --> 00:28:19,907
Hey, go on home now!

331
00:28:20,032 --> 00:28:21,033
What happened?

332
00:28:24,119 --> 00:28:25,704
Go home now.

333
00:28:27,164 --> 00:28:28,540
Go home!

334
00:28:38,425 --> 00:28:39,468
Toshi.

335
00:28:49,394 --> 00:28:51,021
They both went down with a single strike.

336
00:28:53,065 --> 00:28:55,484
As far as I know,
there is only one person capable

337
00:28:57,069 --> 00:28:58,278
of a feat like this.

338
00:29:01,615 --> 00:29:02,658
It's Izo.

339
00:29:06,203 --> 00:29:08,038
I have to find him, and fast.

340
00:29:09,623 --> 00:29:10,666
Do you have any leads?

341
00:29:11,124 --> 00:29:12,167
No.

342
00:29:12,834 --> 00:29:14,336
But he has to be close.

343
00:29:16,838 --> 00:29:18,215
What will you do when you find him?

344
00:29:27,099 --> 00:29:28,100
Cut him down.

345
00:29:33,146 --> 00:29:34,439
Are you really sure about that?

346
00:29:37,276 --> 00:29:42,030
If you fight Izo with a heartless blade,
you'll be no different than a manslayer.

347
00:29:42,155 --> 00:29:44,992
If I don't do this now,
more people will die.

348
00:29:45,117 --> 00:29:46,535
That won't do for you two!

349
00:29:50,122 --> 00:29:51,206
That won't do.

350
00:29:58,630 --> 00:30:02,134
Did you two meet just to kill each other?

351
00:30:04,428 --> 00:30:05,429
Remember...

352
00:30:08,473 --> 00:30:10,183
why you aimed to be the strongest.

353
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:16,315
You two were...

354
00:30:21,236 --> 00:30:22,404
friends.

355
00:30:24,197 --> 00:30:25,282
Right?

356
00:30:31,246 --> 00:30:32,456
Before I'm his friend

357
00:30:34,624 --> 00:30:36,501
I'm the vice-commander
of the Mibu Roshigumi.

358
00:30:53,185 --> 00:30:54,311
Izo.

359
00:31:27,010 --> 00:31:28,178
I've been looking for you...

360
00:31:29,513 --> 00:31:30,555
Izo.

361
00:31:44,653 --> 00:31:45,695
Toshizo.

362
00:31:50,283 --> 00:31:51,368
Hey.

363
00:31:55,247 --> 00:31:56,498
It's been a while.

364
00:32:02,337 --> 00:32:03,338
Toshizo.

365
00:32:10,595 --> 00:32:11,638
What is it?

366
00:32:16,768 --> 00:32:17,769
I'm...

367
00:32:20,689 --> 00:32:21,731
I'm...

368
00:32:25,402 --> 00:32:27,737
I kept cutting down people on command.

369
00:32:30,323 --> 00:32:31,408
And the men I fought

370
00:32:34,286 --> 00:32:35,871
started to look like scarecrows.

371
00:32:39,708 --> 00:32:40,750
Now

372
00:32:42,335 --> 00:32:43,920
I feel nothing when I cut them down.

373
00:32:51,052 --> 00:32:52,596
So, have you lost your heart?

374
00:33:07,110 --> 00:33:08,445
Honestly...

375
00:33:14,951 --> 00:33:16,995
I didn't want to meet you like this.

376
00:33:18,413 --> 00:33:19,456
Don't.

377
00:33:23,919 --> 00:33:25,754
I guess we have no choice, Izo.

378
00:33:26,463 --> 00:33:28,006
Don't, Toshizo.

379
00:33:32,093 --> 00:33:33,762
At least, I'll be the one to cut you down.

380
00:33:39,017 --> 00:33:40,393
I am Mibu Roshigumi Vice-Commander...

381
00:33:42,437 --> 00:33:43,688
Hijikata Toshizo.

382
00:33:46,233 --> 00:33:47,359
Here I come!

383
00:33:57,369 --> 00:34:01,373
I am Izo, the Manslayer.

384
00:34:01,498 --> 00:34:03,416
No, you aren't.

385
00:34:30,735 --> 00:34:32,112
Damn, you're strong.

386
00:34:34,614 --> 00:34:35,865
Interesting.

387
00:34:39,327 --> 00:34:41,246
You're still Izo, through and through.

388
00:34:51,381 --> 00:34:52,757
From here on

389
00:34:54,134 --> 00:34:56,094
I'm just Hijikata Toshizo.

390
00:35:01,933 --> 00:35:04,227
You said it yourself, Izo.

391
00:35:04,352 --> 00:35:07,063
"With wooden swords, we can fight
as many times as we want."

392
00:35:07,731 --> 00:35:09,232
But I guess that's not an option now!

393
00:35:13,737 --> 00:35:17,949
This is a fight to the death.
Our first and last duel.

394
00:35:24,623 --> 00:35:28,460
Izo, after this,
we can never do this again.

395
00:35:29,210 --> 00:35:31,588
There's no greater honor
than to fall by your blade.

396
00:35:32,631 --> 00:35:35,425
I know you feel the same. Izo!

397
00:35:52,609 --> 00:35:54,277
Damn, that hurts!

398
00:35:55,070 --> 00:35:57,364
Hey! How does that feel?
Tell me, does a scarecrow bleed?

399
00:35:59,366 --> 00:36:01,284
What you just cut wasn't
a scarecrow, was it?

400
00:36:02,077 --> 00:36:05,580
See? You feel pain, don't you?

401
00:36:08,625 --> 00:36:10,585
And the man I'm fighting isn't
a scarecrow either.

402
00:36:12,087 --> 00:36:15,715
I'm fighting you! Okada Izo!

403
00:36:28,103 --> 00:36:31,940
Hey, what was it we were striving for

404
00:36:33,650 --> 00:36:34,651
Izo?

405
00:36:52,669 --> 00:36:55,505
To become the strongest man alive,
wasn't it?

406
00:37:33,877 --> 00:37:35,962
I don't need something like this

407
00:37:38,965 --> 00:37:40,592
to duel you, Toshizo.

408
00:38:01,237 --> 00:38:04,741
That's more like it, Izo.

409
00:38:09,913 --> 00:38:11,372
All right.

410
00:38:15,668 --> 00:38:16,753
You can continue

411
00:38:18,463 --> 00:38:19,798
to fight with those.

412
00:38:26,971 --> 00:38:28,014
Boss.

413
00:38:51,621 --> 00:38:52,789
Toshizo.

414
00:38:54,791 --> 00:38:55,959
Bring it on!

415
00:38:59,963 --> 00:39:01,089
Yeah!

416
00:40:06,237 --> 00:40:07,488
I am Okada Izo!

417
00:40:08,031 --> 00:40:13,536
The strongest man in all of Japan!

418
00:40:14,996 --> 00:40:19,459
I'm the greatest samurai in all of Japan!

419
00:40:30,929 --> 00:40:33,473
- I won!
- I won!

420
00:40:45,151 --> 00:40:46,819
Looks like another draw.

421
00:40:47,904 --> 00:40:48,905
Toshizo...

422
00:40:53,076 --> 00:40:54,160
Man...

423
00:40:56,829 --> 00:40:58,831
That was a damn good time.

424
00:41:13,012 --> 00:41:15,098
Hey, Toshizo.

425
00:41:18,393 --> 00:41:19,477
Someday...

426
00:41:21,312 --> 00:41:22,480
Someday...

427
00:41:26,192 --> 00:41:27,527
we'll do this again.

428
00:41:30,947 --> 00:41:32,824
No matter how much I boast of my strength

429
00:41:32,949 --> 00:41:34,867
don't you dare run away next time.

430
00:41:49,966 --> 00:41:52,010
What's wrong with you, Toshizo?

431
00:41:53,928 --> 00:41:55,096
You're one to talk.

432
00:41:58,016 --> 00:42:02,395
No matter where you hide,
no matter where you run

433
00:42:03,604 --> 00:42:08,234
I'll find you
and beat the hell out of you!

434
00:42:15,324 --> 00:42:16,451
Toshizo.

435
00:42:17,952 --> 00:42:21,330
You're a real weirdo.

436
00:42:22,999 --> 00:42:28,921
We just made this incredible promise.
So why are you crying?

437
00:42:30,339 --> 00:42:31,758
Shut up!

438
00:42:33,468 --> 00:42:35,344
You're the one who's crying!

439
00:42:38,389 --> 00:42:39,432
What?

440
00:42:40,516 --> 00:42:42,018
But why?

441
00:42:54,322 --> 00:42:55,531
It's a promise, then.

442
00:43:00,995 --> 00:43:02,080
I promise.

443
00:43:27,021 --> 00:43:29,982
After that, Okada Izo was captured in Kyo

444
00:43:31,109 --> 00:43:32,944
and extradited to the Tosa Domain.

445
00:43:34,821 --> 00:43:40,952
He was imprisoned with Takechi Hanpeita
and the rest of the Tosa Loyalist Party.

446
00:43:44,539 --> 00:43:45,623
Hey...

447
00:43:47,834 --> 00:43:49,001
You...

448
00:43:52,130 --> 00:43:54,006
A wooden sword.

449
00:43:55,341 --> 00:43:57,009
Can you lend one to me?

450
00:44:00,471 --> 00:44:01,806
A wooden sword?

451
00:44:02,974 --> 00:44:05,059
What are you going to do with that?

452
00:44:07,728 --> 00:44:09,063
Toshizo

453
00:44:10,731 --> 00:44:12,108
is waiting for me.

454
00:44:19,699 --> 00:44:21,159
Toshizo

455
00:44:22,869 --> 00:44:24,120
is getting stronger

456
00:44:27,248 --> 00:44:29,041
and waiting for me.

457
00:45:05,786 --> 00:45:08,539
Then, on July 3, 1865

458
00:45:08,664 --> 00:45:14,086
Okada Izo was executed by beheading.

459
00:45:14,879 --> 00:45:17,006
They say he was swinging that wooden sword

460
00:45:17,131 --> 00:45:19,217
right up to his final moment.

461
00:45:29,143 --> 00:45:30,770
I can't believe it.

462
00:45:31,479 --> 00:45:33,564
The man they called "Izo the Manslayer"...

463
00:45:35,149 --> 00:45:37,652
Once in Edo and once in Kyo.

464
00:45:38,236 --> 00:45:42,698
To think that was all it took
to forge such a powerful bond.

465
00:45:45,326 --> 00:45:49,163
That's what it means to cross swords
with your life on the line.

466
00:45:50,206 --> 00:45:53,125
Social status and personal beliefs
don't matter.

467
00:45:54,585 --> 00:45:58,339
You just throw pure strength
at one another.

468
00:46:00,758 --> 00:46:04,553
A battle like that is
every samurai's dream.

469
00:46:06,806 --> 00:46:09,392
I'm envious of a bond like that.

470
00:46:10,226 --> 00:46:11,394
It may

471
00:46:13,020 --> 00:46:15,523
have been the last dream
either of them ever had.

472
00:46:17,525 --> 00:46:19,151
Their last dream?

473
00:46:22,321 --> 00:46:23,614
Sadly...

474
00:46:25,324 --> 00:46:27,785
after that, the battles we fought

475
00:46:30,037 --> 00:46:33,249
were a far cry from any such dream.

476
00:46:41,632 --> 00:46:44,260
Hey, Hijikata, what are you doing?

477
00:46:45,261 --> 00:46:46,304
The corps regulations.

478
00:46:47,263 --> 00:46:49,265
To keep the riffraff in line.

479
00:47:03,029 --> 00:47:05,197
That's just like you, Toshi. I love it.

480
00:47:05,364 --> 00:47:06,866
- You really think so?
- Yeah.

481
00:47:08,617 --> 00:47:10,536
We'll fight and clash

482
00:47:10,661 --> 00:47:12,038
to keep the corps' rules in place.

483
00:47:12,204 --> 00:47:14,832
- "The fight is on!"
- Make sure everyone stays in line.

484
00:47:18,336 --> 00:47:20,087
You didn't have to tear it up, Soji!

485
00:47:20,212 --> 00:47:21,714
I'm impressed you
wrote something so idiotic.

486
00:47:21,839 --> 00:47:23,215
In fact, it's almost brilliant.

487
00:47:24,633 --> 00:47:25,676
Kondo.

488
00:47:30,306 --> 00:47:32,308
Never mind Hijikata's scribbles.

489
00:47:33,184 --> 00:47:34,477
Use this.

490
00:47:36,395 --> 00:47:38,189
Who does he think he is?

491
00:47:38,314 --> 00:47:40,649
Now, now. Let's see what you've got.

492
00:47:45,363 --> 00:47:47,031
"The Corps Code."

493
00:47:50,159 --> 00:47:53,871
"One. Do not stray
from the Way of the samurai.

494
00:47:54,413 --> 00:47:58,542
One. Desertion of the corps is forbidden.

495
00:47:59,377 --> 00:48:03,297
One. You are forbidden
to raise money without authorization.

496
00:48:03,422 --> 00:48:07,885
One. You are forbidden
to involve yourself in litigation.

497
00:48:08,386 --> 00:48:12,890
One. Do not engage in personal fights.

498
00:48:15,434 --> 00:48:17,061
Anyone who violates these articles

499
00:48:20,773 --> 00:48:21,816
must commit seppuku."

500
00:48:23,401 --> 00:48:25,569
That's pretty harsh, isn't it?

501
00:48:25,694 --> 00:48:29,073
Okita, this is no time
for such naive talk.

502
00:48:30,032 --> 00:48:32,326
This isn't Shieikan anymore.

503
00:48:33,202 --> 00:48:35,871
To restore order to the chaos in Kyo

504
00:48:36,330 --> 00:48:38,332
the unity of our corps
is absolutely essential.

505
00:48:39,417 --> 00:48:42,002
But still, seppuku seems extreme.

506
00:48:42,128 --> 00:48:43,254
Yamanami.

507
00:48:44,755 --> 00:48:45,840
What is it?

508
00:48:45,965 --> 00:48:47,466
Are you against it, too?

509
00:48:49,260 --> 00:48:50,594
Add two more rules.

510
00:48:58,185 --> 00:48:59,395
"One.

511
00:49:00,729 --> 00:49:02,773
Draw your sword and fight
until you or your opponent has fallen.

512
00:49:04,859 --> 00:49:05,901
One.

513
00:49:07,445 --> 00:49:08,696
If you fail to kill
and take a wound to your back

514
00:49:08,821 --> 00:49:10,030
it is seppuku."

515
00:49:11,532 --> 00:49:12,825
That means...

516
00:49:14,285 --> 00:49:15,911
once you draw your sword, you must win.

517
00:49:16,036 --> 00:49:17,121
Soji.

518
00:49:19,081 --> 00:49:20,249
This is about resolve.

519
00:49:23,961 --> 00:49:25,713
Without this level of resolve

520
00:49:28,048 --> 00:49:29,675
you can't protect the things that matter.

521
00:49:36,182 --> 00:49:37,391
I...

522
00:49:41,520 --> 00:49:43,439
don't want to lose any more comrades.

523
00:49:47,902 --> 00:49:48,944
That's true.

524
00:49:51,572 --> 00:49:53,449
The stricter these rules are

525
00:49:54,533 --> 00:49:57,703
the more justification we'll have to keep

526
00:49:57,828 --> 00:49:59,747
Serizawa's rogue faction in check.

527
00:50:00,498 --> 00:50:01,790
A just cause.

528
00:50:01,916 --> 00:50:02,958
Yes.

529
00:50:03,501 --> 00:50:05,753
At the very least,
it should slow them down.

530
00:50:07,171 --> 00:50:08,547
- Is it good?
- Yes.

531
00:50:09,590 --> 00:50:11,258
The Corps Code?

532
00:50:13,636 --> 00:50:17,806
"One. Do not stray
from the Way of the samurai.

533
00:50:18,182 --> 00:50:22,436
One. Desertion of the corps is forbidden.

534
00:50:22,561 --> 00:50:23,562
One. You are forbidden
to raise money without authorization."

535
00:50:23,687 --> 00:50:27,816
Yamazaki here can memorize anything
he sees and hears, down to every detail

536
00:50:27,942 --> 00:50:30,194
and is able to recall it perfectly.

537
00:50:31,779 --> 00:50:33,447
- A natural-born spy, huh?
- "One. You are forbidden

538
00:50:33,572 --> 00:50:34,615
to involve yourself in litigation.

539
00:50:35,491 --> 00:50:36,951
Anyone who violates these rules..."

540
00:50:37,159 --> 00:50:38,744
YAMAZAKI SUSUMU

541
00:50:38,869 --> 00:50:40,162
"...Seppuku."

542
00:50:49,630 --> 00:50:51,549
The stricter these rules are

543
00:50:52,174 --> 00:50:55,094
the more justification we'll have
to keep Serizawa's rogue faction

544
00:50:55,594 --> 00:50:57,346
in check.

545
00:50:58,055 --> 00:51:00,432
- This is obviously aimed at us.
- A just cause.

546
00:51:00,558 --> 00:51:01,892
Those bastards.

547
00:51:02,017 --> 00:51:03,269
We have to do something.

548
00:51:03,394 --> 00:51:05,563
I like it. The Corps Code.

549
00:51:05,688 --> 00:51:06,689
What?

550
00:51:06,814 --> 00:51:11,485
But this business about committing seppuku
for breaking it, I don't like.

551
00:51:12,111 --> 00:51:16,407
If we play this right,
we could use it to tighten the noose.

552
00:51:16,532 --> 00:51:17,616
Is that so?

553
00:51:18,158 --> 00:51:19,952
Hey, good work.

554
00:51:20,160 --> 00:51:22,663
Money... Money!

555
00:51:51,775 --> 00:51:54,570
"Half past six.
I'll be waiting at Shinkenji Temple."

556
00:52:02,911 --> 00:52:04,622
Guess who?

